|blank1_name = |blank1_info = |website = |footnotes = }} Misrata ( , Libyan Arabic: ), also known as Misurata or Misratah, is a city in northwestern Libya. It is in the Misrata District. With a population of 281,000, Misrata is the third largest city in Libya, after Tripoli and Benghazi. Misrata University is in the city. == Football clubs == * Asswehly S.C.
